Branson, Jan. 24, 125.
Dear Lulu:-
It hurts me to have to say that the Librarian of the State Library at Harrisburg, Pa., finds no record of Conrad Neuhart there, as having served in the Revolution. He may have been fairly old or crippled. But I do not yet despair. It is possible that there are other records. I do not believe that Harrisburg has the only records. Do you know where the D.R.'s look for their information on such things? I feel nearly sure that old Conrad got into it. Unless, of course, he was crippled. You need a direct descendant through four generations for the D.R., don't you? Then, for that purpose, Conrad is our only chance. The D.A.R.'s, I take it. don't insist upon the direct, four generation business. We must not let up on Conrad. Find out how to go about it. You can do this better than I can, as there is no one here who knows. You probably still have my letter, giving all information about old Conrad. Use that information in further inquiry. Golly, golly, I hope you can land him. There were 14 Neiharts (our <del/> people) in the Revolution; but we have to have Conrad. Do you suppose there might be County records at Reading? or why not write to 
Charles R. Roberts, Secretary,
Lehigh County Hist. Society, 
Allentown, Pa. 
Tell him that Conrad Neuhard or Neuhardt or Conrad Neihard (all the same) living in Reading as early as 1758 and through and after the Revolution, is your great-great-grandfather. Say that you have the records for this, and that you want to know how to determine whether or not this Conrad was in the American Army at any time during the Revolution. I think you may be luckier than I've been. 
No, Lulu, this is not my year to compete for the Pulitzer. I mean, this year is decided next year in May. This year I am not considered, for my book appears in this year. See? 
Don't be discouraged. There's a very good chance that Conrad fought. 
Try also The County Clerk of Bucks Co, Pa. Reading is in Bucks, Also write Congressional Library. 
Later I'll write Congressional Library you try any place you know of. 

