I don't think much of such things. They are to amaze the rabble. Still, I have two chances at winning this year's award (next year's decision). The decision is on books published during the previous year. Mine is not yet in proofs. You see my CEILECTED POETRY (750 pages, one vol.) appears in the Fall. And my WARS appears this spring. Two bully chances. If I dont' win, it will be a joke. There will be nothing to <del/> match the WARS this year. That is hardly a possibility. I know how far the other toads can jump. But I don't know how the judges may be $$$ tied up socially down there. This is a foolish world. Lulu. There was a strong effort to keep the Poetry Society Prize away from me last time. Not one judge wanted to give it to me, but in spite of the outright animosity (personal) of the woman judge (Mrs. Henderson) I won on points. Nobody could agree on any $$$ other book. The fun is in this: that the other books are dead as the Dodo now. Nobody knows the names of them. But my stuf increases and spreads steadily. People are largely fools, Lulu. 
